org.lobobrowser.clientlet

Interface Clientlet

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BadVersionClientlet, BaseCompiledClientlet, CompiledJavaFXClientlet, DownloadClientlet, HtmlClientlet, ImageClientlet, JavaSourceClientlet, PdfClientlet, TextClientlet

    public interface Clientlet
    A clientlet processes a URL response and creates content renderable by a user agent.
    See Also:
    ClientletSelector.select(ClientletRequest, ClientletResponse)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void process(ClientletContext context)
      This method is invoked by a clientlet engine to process a URL response.

    • Method Detail

      • process

        void process(ClientletContext context)
      throws ClientletException
        This method is invoked by a clientlet engine to process a URL response. After the response is processed, the clientlet should either set displayable content via ClientletContext.setResultingContent(ComponentContent) or redirect navigation elsewhere.
        Parameters:
        context - An instance of ClientletContext which represents the current request context.
        Throws:
        ClientletException - This may be thrown by a clientlet when there are document errors.
